
Prospective candidate for the UK Tory party leadership, Kenneth Clarke, is "unfit" for the role because of his continued connection with the tobacco industry, says a contributor to this week's BMJ. MP Kenneth Clarke, deputy chairman of British American Tobacco (BAT) which holds one sixth of the global tobacco market, has been a leading supporter of the industry for well over thirty years, says Mike Daube, a Professor of Health Policy and campaigner for tobacco control... click link for more info.

